{"id":705162,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyde_Park_and_Regent%27s_Park_bombings","text":"e=\"preserve\">The Hyde Park and Regent's Park bombings occurred on 20 July 1982. Members of the Provisional Irish Republican Army used a bomb in each park to attack British military ceremonies in central London.\nIn Hyde Park, a nail bomb in a car exploded. It killed four soldiers and seven horses.\nIn Regent's Park, a bomb underneath a bandstand killed seven military bandsmen.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Volunteer_(Irish_republican)","surface_form":"Members","offset":80},{"uri":"Provisional_Irish_Republican_Army","surface_form":"Provisional Irish Republican Army","offset":95},{"uri":"British_military","surface_form":"British military","offset":164},{"uri":"Central_London","surface_form":"central London","offset":195},{"uri":"Hyde_Park%2C_London","surface_form":"Hyde Park","offset":214},{"uri":"Nail_bomb","surface_form":"nail bomb","offset":227},{"uri":"Car_bomb","surface_form":"car","offset":242},{"uri":"Explode","surface_form":"explode","offset":246},{"uri":"British_Army","surface_form":"soldiers","offset":271},{"uri":"Regent%27s_Park","surface_form":"Regent's Park","offset":301},{"uri":"Bandstand","surface_form":"bandstand","offset":336},{"uri":"Military_band","surface_form":"military band","offset":359}]}